From: jepstei@afterlife.ncsc.mil (John Epstein)
Subject: status report 0.99pl13r and sound driver 2.1
Date: Tue, 23 Nov 1993 01:29:13 GMT

Experience with Xboing 8.1 with linux 0.99 patch 13 and sound driver 1.99.9
was that Xboing lost count of remaining bricks after 5 or 6 screens on the
average.

Recompiling linux 0.99 patch level 13r and naturally sound driver 2.1, since
it is included with patch level 13r, and NOT recompiling anything else,
Xboing now did not lose count of bricks until screen 30 in one case and other
cases I actually lost the game before Xboing lost count of its bricks.

I am sending this to comp.os.linux.development, not comp.os.linux.help as
I do not need help --- just reporting that 0.99pl13r has "fixed" something.

BTW: X11 still crashes with signal 11 about once every two or three hours.
I understand this problem is only with the ET4000 driver.

John


